## Building Model using Text Mining Capability in Oracle Machine Learning 
Oracle Machine Learning not only handles structured data, but also enables automatically building an model based on unstructured data like text. By leveraging Oracle Text functionality, useful features can be automatically extracted from the text column and then picked up to build the model automatically.

In this notebook, we build an SVM model to predict customers most likely to be positive responders to an Affinity Card loyalty program. The data comes with a text column that contains user comments. With a few extra queries, the model automatically utilizes the text column in the dataset and build model on both structured and unstructured columns from the table.

paragraphs.title: Prepare data
paragraphs.text:
%script

CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW mining_data AS
SELECT
 a.CUST_ID, a.CUST_GENDER,
 2003-a.CUST_YEAR_OF_BIRTH AGE,
 a.CUST_MARITAL_STATUS, c.COUNTRY_NAME, a.CUST_INCOME_LEVEL, b.EDUCATION,
 b.OCCUPATION, b.HOUSEHOLD_SIZE, b.YRS_RESIDENCE, b.AFFINITY_CARD,
 b.BULK_PACK_DISKETTES, b.FLAT_PANEL_MONITOR, b.HOME_THEATER_PACKAGE,
 b.BOOKKEEPING_APPLICATION, b.PRINTER_SUPPLIES, b.Y_BOX_GAMES,
 b.os_doc_set_kanji, b.comments 
FROM
 sh.customers a,
 sh.supplementary_demographics b,
 sh.countries c
WHERE
 a.CUST_ID = b.CUST_ID
 AND a.country_id  = c.country_id
 AND a.cust_id between 100001 and 104500;

paragraphs.title: Create the view of train dataset
paragraphs.text:
%script

CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW mining_train_text AS
SELECT *
FROM mining_data
WHERE cust_id between 101501 and 103000;
/
CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW mining_test_text AS
SELECT *
FROM mining_data
WHERE cust_id between 100001 and 101500;
/

paragraphs.title: Check the text column
paragraphs.text:
%sql

SELECT CUST_ID, COMMENTS  
FROM mining_train_text
WHERE COMMENTS IS NOT NULL
